summary: Killing Eve is honestly everything I want in a dark sapphic romance. Or just dark romance in general. I absolutely love the...
body: Killing Eve is honestly everything I want in a dark sapphic romance. Or just dark romance in general. I absolutely love the narrative of monster (Villanelle) bringing out the darkness and the monstrous that already exists in someone seemingly good/innocent (Eve). Though, Eve isn’t exactly good. Their obsessive love is so facinating and I just love watching how ot twists and turns.

summary: if i have to tell one more person  “eve polastri does not exist as a character to fulfill some sort of angelic savior type who...
body:
if i have to tell one more person 

“eve polastri does not exist as a character to fulfill some sort of angelic savior type who will destroy or be seduced to fall from heaven by the devil aka villanelle and in fact eve polastri is supremely flawed, with an almost complete lack of morals, and your perception of eve, a woman currently married to a man, being ‘drawn away’ from good by an openly bisexual evil woman is mildly homophobic, played out, wrong, and i hate it” 

i will riot
